# tunnel.env — the Cloudflare Tunnel credential for the NAS-hosted site. Copy to `tunnel.env`, paste
# your token, chmod 600. NAMES ONLY here (safe to commit); the real file is gitignored and NEVER committed.
#
# Deliberately separate from tape.env so the cloudflared daemon only ever holds the tunnel token —
# it has no business seeing your R2 or LLM keys.
#
# Where the token comes from (see docs/SETUP-NAS-WEB.md, step 1):
#   Cloudflare dashboard → Zero Trust → Networks → Tunnels → Create a tunnel → Cloudflared →
#   name it (e.g. "tape-nas") → the install command it shows you contains `--token eyJ...` →
#   copy JUST that token string.
#
# The token IS a credential: anyone holding it can publish traffic through your tunnel. Treat it like
# a password — chmod 600, never commit, rotate it in the dashboard if it leaks.
TUNNEL_TOKEN=
